      "message": "Yes, in line 106 (of amsterdam) or line 139 (of master) in deleteAll.bash file ~.~\n\nAs mentioned before, this script was created aiming to ensure reaching the desired goal of clean up, hence, set of actions are repeating what have been done in deleteAll.bash, such as this line, as well as line 43 (which repeats line 138 of master or line 1-6 of amsterdam in deleteAll.bash file). \n\nFrom my using of this script, these repeats cleans up when deleteAll.sh was not cleaning properly, and  they do not cause any bad side effects even when deleteAll.sh has done its related actions properly. ~.~",
